svg.metadata: Created by FontForge 20191125 at Fri Sep 7 14:26:01 2012 By convertio DIN PT is a new font family of sans serif typefaces designed in ParaType on the base of well known German font developed in Deutsches Institut fur Normung e.V. (German Institute for Standardization) that was published in 1936 and registered as DIN 1451. The font has remembering geometric design and convey strong feeling of German "ordnung". Due to it naive rude shapes DIN font becomes very popular in the last years and begets enormous modern variations. ParaType version of DIN was developed by Dmitry Kirsanov and released in 2012.
